  "text": "In order to ensure the security of power grid, the power capacity for a PEBFCS is usually adequate for simultaneous charging of all the fast charging piles, otherwise the total power of chargers might exceed the capacity of distribution transformer and the line overload might occur. However, in the actual operation, the total charging power of the PEBFCS seldom hits the upper limit [CITATION_1] . For this reason, installing ESS rather than a distribution transformer with overlarge capacity could be a more economical way by reducing the grid connection fee, i.e., the capacity charge for a PEBFCS.",
